WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:03.000
Hello, colleagues! My name is Natalia Volodina.

00:03.000 --> 00:07.000
I am the Director of the Silvano Fashion Group's Personnel Holdings.

00:07.000 --> 00:10.000
Today we are going to talk about the adaptation of the personnel.

00:10.000 --> 00:14.000
I will share my knowledge and experience gained during my work in Silvano,

00:14.000 --> 00:21.000
in the Moscow Nut Company, after participating in a number of consulting projects on this topic.

00:21.000 --> 00:26.000
What is the adaptation of the personnel?

00:26.000 --> 00:32.000
No matter how expensive the search for a new employee is, the next necessary step is its adaptation.

00:32.000 --> 00:38.000
Sometimes the absence of a system of adaptation in a company or at least a number of elementary adaptation tools

00:38.000 --> 00:42.000
leads to the absence of all the efforts made in advance.

00:42.000 --> 00:48.000
Consultants say that about 80% of people who quit their jobs in the first six months of their work

00:48.000 --> 00:52.000
are the ones who make decisions about it in the first two weeks.

00:52.000 --> 00:54.000
The question is why this happens.

00:54.000 --> 00:57.000
There are several reasons.

00:57.000 --> 01:05.000
One of them is that the reality of the new employee is sometimes not in line with what we told him during the interview.

01:05.000 --> 01:12.000
The second reason is either the informational vacuum that the employee is in,

01:12.000 --> 01:21.000
not even his inability, but our inability to provide him with the necessary information that he needs,

01:21.000 --> 01:26.000
or vice versa, there is too much information that the employee is lost in it.

01:26.000 --> 01:31.000
The adaptation system is one of the elements of the personnel management system.

01:31.000 --> 01:37.000
Nevertheless, we pay attention to it very often on the residual principle.

01:37.000 --> 01:41.000
We train and develop people, we evaluate them, we form a corporate culture.

01:41.000 --> 01:51.000
Nevertheless, the main goal of the personnel adaptation program is to reduce the costs of the organization.

01:51.000 --> 01:53.000
It is important to remember about this economy.

01:53.000 --> 01:56.000
What is the reason for the reduction of the costs of the organization?

01:56.000 --> 02:01.000
The first reason is that our new employee is more likely to take office.

02:01.000 --> 02:10.000
If an employee is more likely to take office, it means that he is going to the level of performance that is necessary in his profession.

02:10.000 --> 02:12.000
Therefore, the first is performance.

02:12.000 --> 02:16.000
The second is a reduction in the number of marriages.

02:16.000 --> 02:24.000
If we approach the adaptation of an employee seriously, we train him, explain everything that he needs,

02:24.000 --> 02:30.000
then the number of possible mistakes in the first days, weeks, months of work is reduced.

02:30.000 --> 02:36.000
The second, in addition to the accelerated process of entering the position, is a reduction in the level of flow of personnel.

02:37.000 --> 02:46.000
The number of people who do not pass the probation period is reduced, as well as those who leave our company in the first six months of work.

02:46.000 --> 02:50.000
Why do we divide probation period and first six months of work?

02:50.000 --> 02:57.000
The probation period is a period when not only the employee, but also the company undergoes a test before the employee.

02:57.000 --> 03:02.000
Here, it is easier for the employee to resign, and it is easier for the company to part with him.

03:03.000 --> 03:08.000
Nevertheless, a number of employees, even realizing that they do not want to continue their career in our companies,

03:08.000 --> 03:15.000
do not leave the company during these three months, so as to, as they explain, not to spoil their record in their workbooks.

03:15.000 --> 03:25.000
Therefore, it is important to understand that one of the indicators that we track when talking about adaptation is how many people have been fired in the first six months, or even a year of work.

03:25.000 --> 03:34.000
Such dismissals can be consequences of improperly adapted systems and improperly used tools.

03:34.000 --> 03:40.000
Of course, there are a number of benefits for the company and for the employee from the implementation of the adaptation system.

03:40.000 --> 03:44.000
Let's see what benefits each party has.

03:45.000 --> 03:59.000
If we talk about the employee, then he is in the presence of a certain ideal situation, which we will strive for, and we would like this system to be in our companies.

03:59.000 --> 04:05.000
If we talk about the employee, then the first benefit is to receive complete information that is required for work.

04:05.000 --> 04:14.000
It is not a search for something, to look up something, someone retold, someone knows, or someone guessed and shared with the employee.

04:14.000 --> 04:18.000
It is exactly the complete objective information that is necessary for work.

04:18.000 --> 04:22.000
The next benefit is a decrease in the level of uncertainty and anxiety.

04:23.000 --> 04:36.000
Psychologists who study the impact of stress in our lives determine that changing jobs is one of the major stress factors.

04:36.000 --> 04:39.000
According to one of the studies, it is in the third place.

04:39.000 --> 04:43.000
In the first place, it is the death of a loved one, and in the second place, it is divorce.

04:43.000 --> 04:44.000
In the third place, it is changing jobs.

04:44.000 --> 04:48.000
It is in such a situation that our task is to support a person.

04:49.000 --> 04:54.000
The next benefit is to improve the satisfaction of work and to develop a positive attitude towards the company.

04:54.000 --> 05:00.000
This is also a benefit for the company, but it is also important for the employee to understand that the choice he made is correct.

05:00.000 --> 05:08.000
Then the employee learns the norms of corporate culture, builds schemes of interaction with colleagues, and always receives feedback.

05:08.000 --> 05:12.000
This is his benefit if the adaptation system exists.

05:12.000 --> 05:14.000
What are the benefits for the company?

05:14.000 --> 05:28.000
First of all, it is the mechanism of assessing the professional and management competencies of the employee, his potential as a result of the first months of work.

05:28.000 --> 05:34.000
When after a few months we understand who joined us, what he can do, what he can do.

05:34.000 --> 05:40.000
Maybe he was overrated at the entrance, when he was selected, he sold himself well, as we say.

05:40.000 --> 05:45.000
Maybe he was underrated, and our task is to correct this mistake.

05:45.000 --> 05:50.000
The next is the identification of shortcomings of the existing selection system.

05:50.000 --> 06:00.000
Very often, in the first few months, those people who should not have joined our company are fired.

06:00.000 --> 06:02.000
Because we made a mistake when selecting.

06:02.000 --> 06:06.000
And, accordingly, with a built-in adaptation system, we will also see.

06:07.000 --> 06:11.000
The next is the possibility of planning the career of a new employee.

06:11.000 --> 06:19.000
In no case should we forget that, in addition to this, we develop, let's say, institutes of mentorship in the company.

06:19.000 --> 06:34.000
Leaders, in the department of which employees come, develop their management competencies related to training, with the provision of feedback, and so on.

06:35.000 --> 06:37.000
This is very important.

06:37.000 --> 06:39.000
But, colleagues, do not forget that these are just benefits.

06:39.000 --> 06:43.000
The main goal is to reduce the costs of the organization.

06:43.000 --> 06:49.000
The question is about the adaptation system, what it is needed for, and, most importantly, when.

06:49.000 --> 06:56.000
As we know from the economic theory, the company goes through several stages during its development.

06:56.000 --> 06:58.000
The first stage is the formation of the company.

06:59.000 --> 07:08.000
At the stage of formation, when the company is still small, when all acquaintances, when all one team, when there is a sense of belonging.

07:08.000 --> 07:18.000
Most likely, there may not be a person who is engaged in the adaptation of new employees, because employees are poured into this team, sometimes a happy team.

07:18.000 --> 07:19.000
But time passes.

07:19.000 --> 07:22.000
And at the stage of formation, it really is so.

07:22.000 --> 07:28.000
Everyone is still together, often sit in some united room, if we are talking about small companies.

07:28.000 --> 07:33.000
And a person, coming to the company, immerses himself in this environment, is imbued.

07:33.000 --> 07:35.000
Everything is available, everything is within reach.

07:35.000 --> 07:37.000
But time passes, companies develop.

07:37.000 --> 07:40.000
And there is a period of intense growth.

07:40.000 --> 07:42.000
New employees appear.

07:42.000 --> 07:45.000
At the time of new employees, more, more, more and more.

07:45.000 --> 07:49.000
And here you have to grab your head, you have to do something.

07:49.000 --> 07:51.000
Because what happens?

07:51.000 --> 07:57.000
What can be the negative consequences of this growth for the company culture?

07:57.000 --> 08:00.000
First of all, information can be lost.

08:00.000 --> 08:04.000
Previously, some employee was irreplaceable, he knew everything.

08:04.000 --> 08:05.000
Without him, the company stopped.

08:05.000 --> 08:10.000
He did not go on vacation, he worked without weekends, because he was a source.

08:10.000 --> 08:12.000
New employees appear.

08:12.000 --> 08:16.000
It is important to take knowledge from this source, which will be necessary for work.

08:17.000 --> 08:22.000
If suddenly our key employee resigns, then knowledge is lost with him.

08:22.000 --> 08:24.000
Therefore, the first is the loss of knowledge.

08:24.000 --> 08:25.000
It is necessary not to allow it.

08:25.000 --> 08:26.000
The second.

08:26.000 --> 08:30.000
The second may be the emergence of subcultures.

08:30.000 --> 08:36.000
Due to the fact that newcomers unite, as if old people are a little far away, they do not pay much attention to them.

08:36.000 --> 08:42.000
And somehow newcomers first went to have lunch, then did something else together.

08:42.000 --> 08:47.000
And over time, the corporate culture of the company that was, it begins to blur.

08:47.000 --> 08:49.000
It does not blur on purpose.

08:49.000 --> 08:51.000
Sometimes it's great, sometimes it's not.

08:51.000 --> 08:54.000
We must decide for ourselves whether we need it.

08:54.000 --> 09:04.000
But it is important to remember that, I repeat again, the emergence of subcultures and the blurring of corporate culture is another consequence.

09:04.000 --> 09:08.000
The absence of an adaptation system during the period of intense growth.

09:08.000 --> 09:14.000
Therefore, during this period of growth, it is necessary to think about the tools, to work out them.

09:14.000 --> 09:16.000
What will it be?

09:16.000 --> 09:18.000
A book for an employee?

09:18.000 --> 09:20.000
Will it be some kind of introductory course?

09:20.000 --> 09:27.000
But some elements that do not require special costs, such as providing a new employee to the team.

09:27.000 --> 09:30.000
Who is he? What will he do? Who will he interact with?

09:30.000 --> 09:32.000
Providing a new employee to the team.

09:32.000 --> 09:35.000
Who is responsible for what? Who is addressed on what issues?

09:36.000 --> 09:42.000
It does not take a lot of time and effort, but sometimes it does not happen in our companies.

09:42.000 --> 09:47.000
An employee comes to his department, he knows who is sitting on the right, who is sitting opposite, who is sitting on his left side.

09:47.000 --> 09:55.000
He does not represent people from other departments at all, who are, let's say, unfamiliar characters to him.

09:55.000 --> 09:59.000
This is a period of intense growth, and it is necessary to think about it.

10:00.000 --> 10:02.000
Once again, who should think about it?

10:02.000 --> 10:06.000
The staff may not be in the service, or there may be one manager per staff.

10:06.000 --> 10:11.000
It is important to remember this about the linear manager, the one whose department employees come to.

10:11.000 --> 10:13.000
The next stage is stabilization.

10:13.000 --> 10:16.000
At the stage of stabilization, everything is already measured.

10:16.000 --> 10:18.000
Newcomers come, old people leave.

10:18.000 --> 10:22.000
This is already a normal, usual, everyday process.

10:22.000 --> 10:28.000
At this stage, it is already appropriate to talk about improving the efficiency of the system.

10:28.000 --> 10:33.000
Maybe something that we did then, during the period of intense growth, is no longer necessary.

10:33.000 --> 10:39.000
Maybe the employee's book, which was created two years ago, has become outdated, and no one looks at it.

10:39.000 --> 10:47.000
At this stage, we are talking about how to improve the efficiency of adaptation tools.

10:47.000 --> 10:55.000
If we have an Internet site with a page for our newcomers, we need to see if newcomers go there, and who goes there.

10:55.000 --> 11:00.000
Maybe we do it for ourselves, as it is sometimes said, when the staff does something for themselves,

11:00.000 --> 11:03.000
and its internal clients and other employees do not use it.

11:03.000 --> 11:05.000
If this is so, it is sad.

11:05.000 --> 11:10.000
And this should be thought about and checked.

11:10.000 --> 11:15.000
At the fourth stage, the stage of decline or crisis, if the company reaches it,

11:15.000 --> 11:20.000
and does not go through the stage of rapid growth again,

11:21.000 --> 11:26.000
the tools lose their efficiency, they do not update, they begin to age,

11:26.000 --> 11:29.000
and it seems that something was, and something is.

11:29.000 --> 11:31.000
And sometimes this leads to a kind of refusal.

11:31.000 --> 11:36.000
Therefore, colleagues, thinking about it, I think you have repeatedly thought about it,

11:36.000 --> 11:40.000
in our companies, in fact, how, is there a system, what is the system?

11:40.000 --> 11:45.000
Always keep in mind that the tools that we adopt,

11:45.000 --> 11:49.000
whether it is adaptation of staff, whether it is training, assessment or something else,

11:49.000 --> 11:57.000
the tools must correspond to the level, that is, the stage of development of our company, which our organization is experiencing.

11:58.000 --> 12:05.000
Adaptation of staff

12:13.000 --> 12:17.000
Colleagues, let's talk about such concepts as adaptation period and trial period.

12:17.000 --> 12:21.000
In literature, these concepts are often found as synonyms.

12:21.000 --> 12:23.000
What is it really?

12:24.000 --> 12:28.000
It is important to remember that the trial period is a legal concept.

12:28.000 --> 12:36.000
And in our country, the duration of the trial period is regulated by the Labor Code.

12:36.000 --> 12:39.000
Adaptation period is something else.

12:39.000 --> 12:41.000
What do specialists say?

12:41.000 --> 12:48.000
Psychologists say that the adaptation period can last from two months to two years.

12:48.000 --> 12:50.000
The period is insane.

12:50.000 --> 12:53.000
What are we talking about today?

12:53.000 --> 12:58.000
About two years, two months, two weeks.

12:58.000 --> 13:04.000
Colleagues, the question that we should answer in our companies is

13:04.000 --> 13:08.000
how long can we shorten the adaptation period of new employees.

13:08.000 --> 13:17.000
Very often, in Russian practice, we equate the adaptation period to the trial period.

13:18.000 --> 13:20.000
It is important to understand whether it is always so.

13:20.000 --> 13:22.000
What is three months?

13:22.000 --> 13:26.000
On the one hand, it is not enough to fully adapt to the team.

13:26.000 --> 13:28.000
On the other hand, let's look at the organization.

13:28.000 --> 13:31.000
Our task is to look at it with such eyes.

13:31.000 --> 13:40.000
Three months pass, and the employee, to whom we have taken on a number of tasks, has not yet reached the level of its performance.

13:40.000 --> 13:42.000
How many companies are ready to lose?

13:42.000 --> 13:45.000
The company is losing money in this period.

13:45.000 --> 13:49.000
The employee does not finish something, does not work on it.

13:49.000 --> 13:51.000
It is not because he does not want to or does not know how to.

13:51.000 --> 13:55.000
It is because he does not succeed or some conditions have not been created.

13:55.000 --> 14:00.000
This issue must be determined within each organization.

14:00.000 --> 14:06.000
It depends on the level of the employee, on the position he occupies.

14:07.000 --> 14:12.000
Today we will talk about the features of adaptation of different categories of employees.

14:12.000 --> 14:19.000
It is important to understand what adaptation activities, what period we take for each of the categories.

14:19.000 --> 14:28.000
There are a number of employees, if they are working employees, who come to ordinary positions, for example, in the production department, in the workshop.

14:29.000 --> 14:41.000
We say that three days, a week, two weeks, no more, because after two weeks we need the process to go and the production not to lose its effectiveness.

14:41.000 --> 14:47.000
If this is an office specialist, a marketing department, let it be a personnel department,

14:47.000 --> 14:55.000
we take a slightly longer period and we are ready to wait a month, wait two, so that the employee reaches the level that is required of him,

14:55.000 --> 14:59.000
and we are ready to learn him along the way, explaining, showing, and so on.

14:59.000 --> 15:04.000
This should not be a chaotic process, it should be planned in advance.

15:04.000 --> 15:09.000
We must understand what, when, from whom we will demand.

15:09.000 --> 15:17.000
Let's talk about when our efforts to adapt the employee begin.

15:17.000 --> 15:20.000
You can highlight a number of stages.

15:20.000 --> 15:27.000
Colleagues, these stages are not a kind of a prescribed truth when we say that do only this way, not in any case.

15:27.000 --> 15:35.000
These are some stages that you define in your company for your employees and say, it is so convenient for us, because it is clear to us.

15:35.000 --> 15:38.000
So, if we talk about the stages.

15:38.000 --> 15:45.000
The first is what we do before the start of the work of a new employee in the company.

15:45.000 --> 15:46.000
What can it be?

15:46.000 --> 15:51.000
It can be, first of all, the preparation of the workplace, the preparation of the plan of his work.

15:51.000 --> 15:53.000
What is the preparation of the workplace?

15:53.000 --> 16:00.000
This is the installation of a computer, at least, this is the search for the place where the employee will sit.

16:00.000 --> 16:09.000
Often, when an employee comes, we say, sit here, we ordered furniture, or we order now, what color do you want?

16:09.000 --> 16:15.000
Most likely, this is not about caring for some color preferences of employees, but about the fact that it was not done.

16:15.000 --> 16:25.000
And the first days, when the same impression is formed, and the same relationship between the company and the employee begins to tie up,

16:25.000 --> 16:34.000
the employee sits at someone's side or at the place of the colleague who is on vacation and feels a little uncomfortable.

16:34.000 --> 16:39.000
So, this is the first thing we do before he appears.

16:39.000 --> 16:41.000
The next period is the introductory one.

16:41.000 --> 16:44.000
This is the first day of the work of a new employee.

16:44.000 --> 16:50.000
We must understand what should happen to him on the first day, who he will meet, when he will meet, what to learn.

16:50.000 --> 16:55.000
And not just a registration in the personnel department, which is very often limited.

16:55.000 --> 17:01.000
It seems that he came, he was told a little about the company, the instruction was definitely carried out in safety techniques,

17:01.000 --> 17:03.000
well, it seems that he was introduced to the course of the case.

17:03.000 --> 17:05.000
Colleagues, this is not enough.

17:05.000 --> 17:08.000
Therefore, the first day of a new employee, he must be prepared.

17:08.000 --> 17:13.000
We will talk about who should do this, the staff or the personnel, the line manager, the mentor.

17:13.000 --> 17:17.000
It depends on the size of the company, on its structure.

17:17.000 --> 17:19.000
Now we are talking about what it should be.

17:19.000 --> 17:21.000
The next period is the introductory one.

17:21.000 --> 17:23.000
This is the first week of work in the company.

17:23.000 --> 17:32.000
These are the most intense weeks in terms of getting information from the person who came to us.

17:32.000 --> 17:41.000
How we will give him, in what volume, in what terms, in what pace, depends on how he perceives it.

17:41.000 --> 17:48.000
Therefore, at this stage, there may be some introductory courses or welcome training.

17:48.000 --> 17:51.000
Welcome training, which we will also talk about.

17:51.000 --> 17:58.000
These are the instructors, this is communication with the managers, with the key employees with whom he will interact.

17:58.000 --> 18:02.000
This is work with databases.

18:02.000 --> 18:12.000
This can be an intranet database, if we have placed all the necessary documentation for work there, or something in print.

18:12.000 --> 18:17.000
This is already work according to the plan that is made for him.

18:17.000 --> 18:21.000
The next is the introduction to the position.

18:21.000 --> 18:23.000
This is the biggest period.

18:23.000 --> 18:27.000
And most often it is occupied by professional training.

18:27.000 --> 18:34.000
When an employee begins to learn during work, interacting with an instructor or a direct manager.

18:34.000 --> 18:37.000
Or when we organize a specific training for him.

18:37.000 --> 18:41.000
If we are talking about the operator of the call center,

18:41.000 --> 18:47.000
who is required to go to training in order to learn the standards that are adopted in the company.

18:47.000 --> 18:51.000
The next period is the evaluation and final one.

18:52.000 --> 18:55.000
The moment of the end of the trial period,

18:55.000 --> 19:00.000
we have already discussed that the trial period and the adaptation period are often compared.

19:00.000 --> 19:06.000
This process must be somehow noted, because the results of the work must be summed up.

19:06.000 --> 19:14.000
How does the employee work, is all the information brought to him, how does he perform his direct duties.

19:14.000 --> 19:18.000
The evaluation period is mandatory.

19:18.000 --> 19:23.000
This does not mean that this is a kind of event or event.

19:23.000 --> 19:27.000
This is a conversation between an employee and a manager.

19:27.000 --> 19:30.000
Very often this is not the case.

19:30.000 --> 19:33.000
It seems that three months have passed, it seems that he is working.

19:33.000 --> 19:36.000
Let him work further, and then we'll see.

19:36.000 --> 19:43.000
Nevertheless, this period of dialogue, a period of conversation for an employee who has ceased to be new,

19:43.000 --> 19:45.000
he has already worked for several months.

19:45.000 --> 19:50.000
This is a period and an opportunity to ask questions to your direct manager.

19:50.000 --> 19:53.000
For the manager, this is an opportunity to give feedback.

19:53.000 --> 20:02.000
Let's talk about the aspects of adaptation, which are discussed by specialists and authors in the field of personnel management.

20:02.000 --> 20:04.000
There are four of them.

20:04.000 --> 20:09.000
The organizational aspect, the social-psychological, the professional and the psychophysiological.

20:09.000 --> 20:12.000
What is it? What is it really?

20:12.000 --> 20:14.000
In fact, everything is very simple.

20:14.000 --> 20:17.000
The first is the inclusion of an employee in an organization.

20:17.000 --> 20:19.000
The second is his inclusion in a team.

20:19.000 --> 20:21.000
And the third is his inclusion in a profession.

20:21.000 --> 20:23.000
Let's look at these aspects in order.

20:23.000 --> 20:25.000
So, organizational adaptation.

20:25.000 --> 20:31.000
Organizational adaptation is responsible for the employee getting answers to his questions

20:31.000 --> 20:35.000
related to the activities of the organization in which he got.

20:35.000 --> 20:38.000
What are the strategic goals and priorities of the company?

20:38.000 --> 20:40.000
How is management carried out?

20:40.000 --> 20:42.000
How are business processes established?

20:42.000 --> 20:44.000
How are decisions made?

20:44.000 --> 20:46.000
What is the structure?

20:46.000 --> 20:50.000
How is the meeting, meeting and so on?

20:50.000 --> 20:52.000
How does the organization live?

20:52.000 --> 20:56.000
Each organization has its own rules and standards.

20:56.000 --> 21:00.000
It is important to have an opportunity to provide this information to the employee.

21:00.000 --> 21:05.000
Very often it happens, let's say, by instinct.

21:05.000 --> 21:08.000
The employee begins to absorb and look at the sides.

21:08.000 --> 21:11.000
What are the strategic goals?

21:11.000 --> 21:14.000
Look on the Internet, answer a colleague at work.

21:14.000 --> 21:17.000
Or read a newspaper if it is a large public company.

21:17.000 --> 21:20.000
In fact, these are the answers that the company has.

21:20.000 --> 21:23.000
And they should be, let's say, formalized.

21:23.000 --> 21:26.000
The employee should have the opportunity to familiarize himself with them.

21:26.000 --> 21:30.000
It's great if the company has local regulatory acts

21:30.000 --> 21:34.000
dedicated to, let's say, how the budgeting process is going on.

21:34.000 --> 21:38.000
This is very important for the line manager or the head of the department

21:38.000 --> 21:40.000
who comes to the company.

21:40.000 --> 21:44.000
But he should learn this from some documents.

21:44.000 --> 21:47.000
And not that someone told him something, by the way.

21:47.000 --> 21:52.000
That by the 20th of the coming month we are making a budget,

21:52.000 --> 21:55.000
send it, there is a vote, a budget committee and so on.

21:55.000 --> 22:00.000
This is not the information that needs to be absorbed from the air.

22:00.000 --> 22:02.000
Colleagues, it should be.

22:02.000 --> 22:05.000
The next is social and psychological adaptation.

22:05.000 --> 22:09.000
This is getting to know the corporate culture of the company.

22:09.000 --> 22:14.000
This is an answer for the employee to the question

22:14.000 --> 22:18.000
what are they, what is the company, what will I be like.

22:18.000 --> 22:21.000
This is a very important aspect, because it is a joining of the team.

22:21.000 --> 22:25.000
In any team, in any department, there are already their own norms,

22:25.000 --> 22:28.000
their own rules, their own standards.

22:28.000 --> 22:30.000
What do we do? We are like this.

22:30.000 --> 22:33.000
And this is what the employee should familiarize himself with.

22:33.000 --> 22:35.000
How do we live? Why do we live like this?

22:35.000 --> 22:39.000
Because if we are talking about a joint professional life,

22:39.000 --> 22:42.000
this person who came to us should share it.

22:42.000 --> 22:47.000
The next is professional adaptation or getting a job.

22:47.000 --> 22:51.000
This aspect can also be called pre-training.

22:51.000 --> 22:55.000
That is, acquiring the knowledge and skills that the employee lacks.

22:55.000 --> 22:59.000
It is not a secret that very often we take people who,

22:59.000 --> 23:02.000
we say, this is our person.

23:02.000 --> 23:05.000
It's okay that he doesn't know a little, we will teach him.

23:05.000 --> 23:08.000
If we decided to do this during the interview, then we must teach him.

23:08.000 --> 23:11.000
He should not have time to learn by himself,

23:11.000 --> 23:13.000
but we must do something for him.

23:13.000 --> 23:17.000
We must organize some courses or seminars.

23:17.000 --> 23:20.000
If we do not have such an opportunity, because we are a small company,

23:20.000 --> 23:24.000
then we must include him in the project, where he should understand.

23:24.000 --> 23:29.000
We must offer him to work with a mentor.

23:30.000 --> 23:33.000
It does not matter that the mentor is not a dedicated department,

23:33.000 --> 23:35.000
but his neighbor.

23:35.000 --> 23:38.000
The neighbor, on the other hand, knows his mission and mentorship.

23:38.000 --> 23:42.000
He prompts, explains and does it purposefully.

23:42.000 --> 23:46.000
And not just like that, let's say, in a friendly way, somehow in a neighborly way.

23:46.000 --> 23:49.000
Therefore, this is a professional adaptation, pre-training.

23:49.000 --> 23:54.000
Sometimes such concepts are included in this aspect,

23:54.000 --> 23:56.000
that it seems that the employee came prepared.

23:56.000 --> 23:58.000
For example, we are a large trading company,

23:58.000 --> 24:04.000
we hire a supervisor, a specialist from the side with experience of working in such a position.

24:04.000 --> 24:08.000
But it is important to remember that the supervisor,

24:08.000 --> 24:10.000
as a linear leader of the trading team,

24:10.000 --> 24:13.000
will train managers by personnel.

24:13.000 --> 24:17.000
And it is important that he teaches them the way we teach in the company,

24:17.000 --> 24:19.000
and not the way he was taught somewhere, sometime.

24:19.000 --> 24:24.000
Therefore, during the period of professional adaptation,

24:24.000 --> 24:29.000
we send this supervisor to some seminars,

24:29.000 --> 24:34.000
or he gets acquainted with some methodological materials

24:34.000 --> 24:36.000
on the topic with which he will work.

24:36.000 --> 24:39.000
That is, he gets acquainted with the standards,

24:39.000 --> 24:41.000
and learns from them.

24:41.000 --> 24:44.000
The next is psychophysiological adaptation.

24:44.000 --> 24:50.000
In fact, this is the adaptation of an employee

24:50.000 --> 24:55.000
to a certain and often different from the usual working regime.

24:55.000 --> 24:57.000
What can it be?

24:57.000 --> 24:59.000
Let's look at some examples.

24:59.000 --> 25:01.000
It can be a shift schedule.

25:01.000 --> 25:05.000
A young specialist comes to us who has never worked a shift.

25:05.000 --> 25:08.000
Why did we decide that he would be easy to work at night?

25:08.000 --> 25:12.000
This is a different way of life for those people

25:12.000 --> 25:16.000
who work 2 hours in 2 days, 3 hours in 3 days, it does not matter how.

25:16.000 --> 25:19.000
Day and night, they change places.

25:19.000 --> 25:22.000
It is difficult. Can an employee work like that?

25:22.000 --> 25:27.000
The next is a shifted work schedule.

25:27.000 --> 25:30.000
Someone starts working very early, and finishes earlier.

25:30.000 --> 25:32.000
Or starts later, and finishes later.

25:32.000 --> 25:35.000
It is important to understand whether a person is ready for this.

25:35.000 --> 25:38.000
Of course, we remember this in case we have such conditions,

25:38.000 --> 25:41.000
and we take people in such conditions.

25:41.000 --> 25:44.000
The next is an unregulated working day.

25:44.000 --> 25:48.000
Colleagues, we all say that we are ready to work unregulated.

25:48.000 --> 25:52.000
Internal readiness is one thing, internal possibilities are another.

25:52.000 --> 25:56.000
The next is a long business trip.

25:56.000 --> 25:59.000
If we take a person and say that he will have business trips,

25:59.000 --> 26:02.000
he says, super, I always dreamed of seeing my country,

26:02.000 --> 26:04.000
neighboring countries, and so on.

26:04.000 --> 26:07.000
It is necessary to understand what will happen in a month,

26:07.000 --> 26:09.000
in 2, in 3 of his long business trips.

26:09.000 --> 26:11.000
For one, it will really be super,

26:11.000 --> 26:14.000
and for another, it will be some kind of tension,

26:14.000 --> 26:17.000
some kind of dissatisfaction that will accumulate, accumulate, accumulate, and accumulate.

26:18.000 --> 26:20.000
It is also worth thinking about.

26:20.000 --> 26:25.000
The next example is, let's say, a project work.

26:25.000 --> 26:28.000
People who work in a measured mode,

26:28.000 --> 26:33.000
solving tasks, or, let's say, similar tasks, day by day,

26:33.000 --> 26:35.000
do not always fit into the project.

26:35.000 --> 26:40.000
Projects are very often characterized by burning deadlines,

26:40.000 --> 26:43.000
when before a certain deadline we are straining,

26:43.000 --> 26:45.000
working day and night, but we are doing something.

26:45.000 --> 26:48.000
Again, it is not for everyone, it can be comfortable and convenient.

26:48.000 --> 26:50.000
These are just a number of examples,

26:50.000 --> 26:52.000
there may be something else in your companies.

26:52.000 --> 26:55.000
Think, look around, look at what is there,

26:55.000 --> 26:58.000
from the point of view of the labor regime in our case,

26:58.000 --> 27:02.000
if we are talking about psychological, physiological adaptation,

27:02.000 --> 27:06.000
something that can cause some kind of tension,

27:06.000 --> 27:08.000
not even dissatisfaction.

27:08.000 --> 27:11.000
Sometimes an employee says, I liked working with you,

27:11.000 --> 27:14.000
thanks, good team, good company,

27:14.000 --> 27:16.000
but I can't, it's difficult for me,

27:16.000 --> 27:18.000
health, something else, and so on.

27:18.000 --> 27:21.000
So keep this in mind.

27:21.000 --> 27:24.000
If we are talking about the adaptation system today,

27:24.000 --> 27:28.000
then we must understand that this is a kind of a set of elements.

27:28.000 --> 27:31.000
And the management of the adaptation system involves several stages.

27:31.000 --> 27:35.000
Colleagues, adaptation as a corporate culture,

27:35.000 --> 27:37.000
even if we do not do it,

27:37.000 --> 27:39.000
we cannot say that we do not have a corporate culture.

27:39.000 --> 27:42.000
It is as it has developed, it is.

27:42.000 --> 27:45.000
We also cannot say that we do not have adaptation.

27:45.000 --> 27:50.000
Employees somehow join the team, the company, and so on.

27:50.000 --> 27:52.000
So, this is how it happened,

27:52.000 --> 27:54.000
a kind of chaotic process, it exists.

27:54.000 --> 27:56.000
It exists now, in any company, you too.

27:56.000 --> 27:58.000
And if you start thinking about it,

27:58.000 --> 28:01.000
first, analyze the current situation.

28:01.000 --> 28:03.000
Look what is there.

28:03.000 --> 28:07.000
This is a very good advice for those personnel specialists

28:07.000 --> 28:10.000
who come to a new job, to a new company themselves.

28:10.000 --> 28:14.000
By the way, very often in literature you can find thoughts

28:14.000 --> 28:17.000
that a bootlegger is without boots.

28:17.000 --> 28:21.000
When HR or a personnel manager comes to a company,

28:21.000 --> 28:23.000
no one is doing his adaptation,

28:23.000 --> 28:25.000
he somehow adapts himself.

28:25.000 --> 28:28.000
This really happens.

28:28.000 --> 28:30.000
But, thank God, not in all companies.

28:30.000 --> 28:33.000
Therefore, if you are the same personnel manager

28:33.000 --> 28:35.000
who came to the company,

28:35.000 --> 28:39.000
well, do not think about yourself.

28:39.000 --> 28:42.000
If you have already come to the conditions you are in,

28:42.000 --> 28:49.000
look around, look how other employees are adapting to your company.

28:49.000 --> 28:51.000
It will be easy for you to do it,

28:51.000 --> 28:54.000
because you are a newbie yourself in such a situation.

28:54.000 --> 28:56.000
Therefore, the first thing is to analyze the current situation.

28:56.000 --> 28:58.000
We looked, analyzed.

28:58.000 --> 29:02.000
The next thing is to determine the procedures that are really needed.

29:02.000 --> 29:04.000
The determination of the procedure, colleagues,

29:04.000 --> 29:06.000
depends on the stage of the company's development,

29:06.000 --> 29:08.000
on the goals in the area of personnel management.

29:08.000 --> 29:11.000
After that, we determined the third stage.

29:11.000 --> 29:13.000
We develop and implement.

29:13.000 --> 29:17.000
And the fourth stage is the assessment of efficiency.

29:17.000 --> 29:20.000
Because you can develop and implement a lot.

29:20.000 --> 29:22.000
How effective is it for us?

29:22.000 --> 29:25.000
So, let's go in order.

29:25.000 --> 29:27.000
Analysis of the current situation.

29:27.000 --> 29:31.000
What are the auditing methods?

29:31.000 --> 29:35.000
When, with very often limited time resources,

29:36.000 --> 29:38.000
when there are no budgets,

29:38.000 --> 29:40.000
you can still do something.

29:40.000 --> 29:42.000
Let's see what methods are.

29:42.000 --> 29:45.000
The first is the analysis of documents and local regulatory acts

29:45.000 --> 29:49.000
that regulate adaptation procedures.

29:49.000 --> 29:51.000
This is really a method.

29:51.000 --> 29:53.000
But it is important to understand,

29:53.000 --> 29:55.000
and in my experience I have encountered situations

29:55.000 --> 29:57.000
when there is a situation of adaptation.

29:57.000 --> 29:59.000
You think, that's cool.

29:59.000 --> 30:01.000
In life, you ask questions, and they say,

30:01.000 --> 30:03.000
well, there is, but it doesn't work somehow.

30:03.000 --> 30:05.000
We do what we do.

30:05.000 --> 30:08.000
Therefore, analyzing, you need to understand,

30:08.000 --> 30:10.000
if such a document already exists,

30:10.000 --> 30:13.000
then it is about what was thought about.

30:13.000 --> 30:17.000
And so, when you analyze what you will read,

30:17.000 --> 30:19.000
what you will see,

30:19.000 --> 30:21.000
you will understand whether there are gaps or not.

30:21.000 --> 30:23.000
Whether there is a discrepancy or not.

30:23.000 --> 30:25.000
The next is observation.

30:25.000 --> 30:27.000
Observe how it all happens around you.

30:27.000 --> 30:30.000
The next is an interview or conversations.

30:30.000 --> 30:32.000
Who can you talk to?

30:32.000 --> 30:34.000
You can talk to employees

30:34.000 --> 30:36.000
who have been hired in the company

30:36.000 --> 30:38.000
up to six months ago.

30:38.000 --> 30:41.000
Those who remember how it was with them.

30:41.000 --> 30:44.000
This is a conversation with employees

30:44.000 --> 30:47.000
who are fired after less than a year.

30:47.000 --> 30:48.000
Remember?

30:48.000 --> 30:50.000
Those who do not want to spoil the work record,

30:50.000 --> 30:53.000
but can no longer work with us for some reason.

30:53.000 --> 30:55.000
This is an interview with managers,

30:55.000 --> 30:58.000
whose divisions have a large set of staff.

30:58.000 --> 31:00.000
What do they do with people?

31:00.000 --> 31:01.000
How do they work?

31:01.000 --> 31:02.000
Who works with them?

31:02.000 --> 31:05.000
Managers are a very good source of information.

31:05.000 --> 31:08.000
These are our direct clients,

31:08.000 --> 31:10.000
internal clients in the company.

31:10.000 --> 31:11.000
We work with them.

31:11.000 --> 31:15.000
The next is a focus group with experts.

31:15.000 --> 31:17.000
Under the experts, we understand

31:17.000 --> 31:19.000
the staff of the department,

31:19.000 --> 31:20.000
the same managers,

31:20.000 --> 31:22.000
the same leading employees of other departments.

31:22.000 --> 31:24.000
When we get together and ask a question

31:24.000 --> 31:26.000
about how it is, whether it is correct,

31:26.000 --> 31:27.000
whether it works.

31:27.000 --> 31:29.000
Why doesn't it work if it is so?

31:29.000 --> 31:31.000
The next is a survey.

31:31.000 --> 31:33.000
The so-called pulse survey.

31:33.000 --> 31:36.000
During internal corporate research,

31:36.000 --> 31:39.000
there is such a practice in your companies,

31:39.000 --> 31:42.000
a small block is included for employees

31:42.000 --> 31:44.000
who have worked less than half a year

31:44.000 --> 31:46.000
with certain questions.

31:46.000 --> 31:48.000
The advantage of this method is

31:48.000 --> 31:53.000
that we can cover almost 100% of the target audience.

31:53.000 --> 31:57.000
The disadvantage is that we will not ask enough questions.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.000
Perhaps they will not tell us

31:59.000 --> 32:01.000
what they could tell us during the interview.

32:01.000 --> 32:02.000
Because during the survey,

32:02.000 --> 32:04.000
we will not write down the questions,

32:04.000 --> 32:05.000
we will not guess.

32:05.000 --> 32:09.000
The next point is what to ask.

32:09.000 --> 32:11.000
Here is the manager,

32:11.000 --> 32:16.000
here are the employees who have worked for half a year,

32:16.000 --> 32:17.000
and so on.

32:17.000 --> 32:18.000
What do we ask?

32:18.000 --> 32:22.000
The first question is whether the importance of adaptation

32:22.000 --> 32:26.000
is understood by linear managers.

32:26.000 --> 32:28.000
What do managers think about this question?

32:28.000 --> 32:29.000
They say,

32:29.000 --> 32:30.000
why do we need it?

32:30.000 --> 32:32.000
He came and came, let him work,

32:32.000 --> 32:35.000
and they are glad that we invited him.

32:35.000 --> 32:38.000
Or they understand that something needs to be done,

32:38.000 --> 32:40.000
even if he is glad that we invited him.

32:40.000 --> 32:42.000
The next question is who is responsible

32:42.000 --> 32:44.000
for the adaptation process of a new employee.

32:44.000 --> 32:45.000
Who exactly?

32:45.000 --> 32:48.000
The manager, the mentor, the staff service,

32:48.000 --> 32:51.000
the manager in the only person who does everything,

32:52.000 --> 32:53.000
as it sometimes happens,

32:53.000 --> 32:55.000
and is responsible for it too.

32:55.000 --> 32:57.000
If not,

32:57.000 --> 33:00.000
how are the roles of the staff service

33:00.000 --> 33:02.000
and the roles of the departments

33:02.000 --> 33:04.000
in the process of adaptation?

33:04.000 --> 33:09.000
The next question is how much the introduction to the position

33:09.000 --> 33:12.000
and the whole procedure is differentiated

33:12.000 --> 33:15.000
by the hierarchy of the profession.

33:15.000 --> 33:18.000
How different are we in the company

33:18.000 --> 33:20.000
to the specialists of different departments?

33:20.000 --> 33:22.000
Do we have this or not?

33:22.000 --> 33:23.000
Next,

33:23.000 --> 33:25.000
who defines the mentor for the employee?

33:25.000 --> 33:26.000
And in general,

33:26.000 --> 33:29.000
is it interesting to be a mentor in the company?

33:29.000 --> 33:32.000
Do the people who are already working

33:32.000 --> 33:36.000
want to become mentors for the new ones?

33:36.000 --> 33:38.000
Or is it a headache that says,

33:38.000 --> 33:40.000
God, someone again, and again me?

33:40.000 --> 33:43.000
The leading employee with the internship says,

33:43.000 --> 33:45.000
because he really knows everything,

33:45.000 --> 33:47.000
and we have no one but him.

33:47.000 --> 33:48.000
And for him,

33:48.000 --> 33:52.000
it's a breath of relief every time.

33:52.000 --> 33:53.000
And he,

33:53.000 --> 33:56.000
being a very loyal to our company,

33:56.000 --> 33:58.000
goes to the internship every time.

33:58.000 --> 34:00.000
This is a bad indicator.

34:02.000 --> 34:05.000
What is included in the complex of adaptation?

34:05.000 --> 34:08.000
What tools are developed?

34:08.000 --> 34:11.000
How often are they updated?

34:11.000 --> 34:15.000
How do we evaluate the whole procedure?

34:16.000 --> 34:18.000
Have we achieved the goal we wanted?

34:18.000 --> 34:19.000
Or not?

34:19.000 --> 34:21.000
How is the effectiveness of the event evaluated?

34:21.000 --> 34:22.000
These are the questions.

34:22.000 --> 34:24.000
Again, it's a series of questions.

34:24.000 --> 34:26.000
I've given you several of them.

34:26.000 --> 34:28.000
There can be one and a half times more,

34:28.000 --> 34:29.000
or two times more.

34:29.000 --> 34:31.000
They can be completely different.

34:31.000 --> 34:33.000
But the information must be collected

34:33.000 --> 34:35.000
to understand how we live.

34:35.000 --> 34:38.000
I've given you only a few questions as an example.

34:38.000 --> 34:40.000
They can be completely different.

34:40.000 --> 34:43.000
Your task as a personnel specialist

34:43.000 --> 34:46.000
is to find the most complete answers

34:46.000 --> 34:49.000
to the questions about the adaptation procedure

34:49.000 --> 34:51.000
in our company.

34:51.000 --> 34:52.000
So,

34:52.000 --> 34:54.000
we've analyzed the current situation

34:54.000 --> 34:56.000
in our company.

34:56.000 --> 34:59.000
Our next task is

34:59.000 --> 35:02.000
to determine the list of tools we need.

35:02.000 --> 35:06.000
There are several approaches to choosing tools.

35:06.000 --> 35:10.000
The first one is the so-called problem-oriented approach.

35:10.000 --> 35:11.000
When the thunder rumbles,

35:11.000 --> 35:13.000
when we realize that something has happened,

35:13.000 --> 35:15.000
we need to fix it.

35:15.000 --> 35:17.000
This is the so-called reactive approach.

35:17.000 --> 35:18.000
It's not always good.

35:18.000 --> 35:21.000
It's better to predict, anticipate and understand.

35:21.000 --> 35:24.000
Some people say it's better to do it later than never.

35:24.000 --> 35:27.000
But if we have an opportunity to work for the future

35:27.000 --> 35:28.000
and be proactive,

35:28.000 --> 35:30.000
we need to be proactive.

35:30.000 --> 35:33.000
The next one is the process-oriented approach.

35:33.000 --> 35:34.000
It should be like this.

35:34.000 --> 35:35.000
Everyone has it.

35:35.000 --> 35:37.000
Yesterday I was at a conference

35:37.000 --> 35:39.000
and I was told that it should be like this,

35:39.000 --> 35:41.000
like this, like this in a company.

35:41.000 --> 35:43.000
I liked it and I like the company.

35:43.000 --> 35:45.000
Let's do the same.

35:45.000 --> 35:48.000
When borrowing such tools,

35:48.000 --> 35:49.000
it's great, it's important.

35:49.000 --> 35:51.000
We borrow a lot from each other's experience.

35:51.000 --> 35:53.000
But it's important to understand

35:53.000 --> 35:55.000
whether the thing that works well

35:55.000 --> 35:57.000
in my friend's company

35:57.000 --> 35:59.000
will work for us.

35:59.000 --> 36:00.000
Maybe it will.

36:00.000 --> 36:02.000
The main thing is whether it's necessary for my company.

36:02.000 --> 36:04.000
The next one is the goal-oriented approach.

36:04.000 --> 36:06.000
Let's say, this is our approach.

36:06.000 --> 36:08.000
This is the right approach.

36:08.000 --> 36:10.000
When there are certain goals

36:10.000 --> 36:13.000
in the area of staff management,

36:13.000 --> 36:15.000
which are, let's say,

36:15.000 --> 36:17.000
the consequence of the goals

36:17.000 --> 36:19.000
of the company itself,

36:19.000 --> 36:20.000
the goals of development.

36:20.000 --> 36:22.000
And within this,

36:22.000 --> 36:24.000
we determine what we need,

36:24.000 --> 36:26.000
how we need to do it.

