01:46:47.000 --> 01:46:49.000
When we train an employee

01:46:49.000 --> 01:46:51.000
with new knowledge and skills,

01:46:51.000 --> 01:46:53.000
we need to think about

01:46:53.000 --> 01:46:55.000
how to assess

01:46:55.000 --> 01:46:57.000
the effectiveness of this training.

01:46:57.000 --> 01:46:59.000
The best tool, colleagues,

01:46:59.000 --> 01:47:01.000
that we have today

01:47:01.000 --> 01:47:03.000
is the methodology of Donald Kirkpatrick,

01:47:03.000 --> 01:47:05.000
one of the Western consultants

01:47:05.000 --> 01:47:07.000
in the field of personnel management.

01:47:07.000 --> 01:47:09.000
Sometimes this model is called

01:47:09.000 --> 01:47:11.000
four-dimensional, four-factor.

01:47:11.000 --> 01:47:13.000
That is not the point.

01:47:13.000 --> 01:47:15.000
It is important to remember its content

01:47:15.000 --> 01:47:17.000
and use this model

01:47:17.000 --> 01:47:19.000
when assessing the training.

01:47:19.000 --> 01:47:21.000
Let's recall what it is.

01:47:21.000 --> 01:47:23.000
Whatever we do,

01:47:23.000 --> 01:47:25.000
whether it is a welcome training

01:47:25.000 --> 01:47:27.000
or training of some basics of work,

01:47:27.000 --> 01:47:29.000
it is always important to understand the first thing.

01:47:29.000 --> 01:47:31.000
It is important to assess

01:47:31.000 --> 01:47:33.000
the reaction of the trained.

01:47:33.000 --> 01:47:35.000
Usually, we do it with a questionnaire

01:47:35.000 --> 01:47:37.000
when we ask questions

01:47:37.000 --> 01:47:39.000
and ask what we liked, what we did not like,

01:47:39.000 --> 01:47:41.000
what was easy, what was not enough.

01:47:41.000 --> 01:47:43.000
We often stop at this point.

01:47:43.000 --> 01:47:45.000
We say,

01:47:45.000 --> 01:47:47.000
the training was great,

01:47:47.000 --> 01:47:49.000
but look at the highest marks

01:47:49.000 --> 01:47:51.000
on the questionnaire.

01:47:51.000 --> 01:47:53.000
But wait.

01:47:53.000 --> 01:47:55.000
We need to understand

01:47:55.000 --> 01:47:57.000
that at the first level

01:47:57.000 --> 01:47:59.000
there is only an assessment of the attitude,

01:47:59.000 --> 01:48:01.000
the impression of the participant,

01:48:01.000 --> 01:48:03.000
the training participant

01:48:03.000 --> 01:48:05.000
or the training program itself.

01:48:07.000 --> 01:48:09.000
We can listen

01:48:11.000 --> 01:48:13.000
to a lecture

01:48:13.000 --> 01:48:15.000
of a great coach.

01:48:15.000 --> 01:48:17.000
He will tell you how he worked.

01:48:17.000 --> 01:48:19.000
It will be very interesting.

01:48:19.000 --> 01:48:21.000
But it does not mean

01:48:21.000 --> 01:48:23.000
that we will have some knowledge

01:48:23.000 --> 01:48:25.000
about how to play football.

01:48:25.000 --> 01:48:27.000
And we will not become football players.

01:48:27.000 --> 01:48:29.000
It is important to remember

01:48:29.000 --> 01:48:31.000
that even if the first assessment

01:48:31.000 --> 01:48:33.000
is positive,

01:48:33.000 --> 01:48:35.000
it is only the beginning.

01:48:35.000 --> 01:48:37.000
The next step is the assessment of knowledge,

01:48:37.000 --> 01:48:39.000
the understanding

01:48:39.000 --> 01:48:41.000
of what is left in the heads of the trained.

01:48:41.000 --> 01:48:43.000
It is very important

01:48:43.000 --> 01:48:45.000
when it comes to professional training.

01:48:45.000 --> 01:48:47.000
The next level is the assessment

01:48:47.000 --> 01:48:49.000
of behavior at work.

01:48:49.000 --> 01:48:51.000
How does a person apply

01:48:51.000 --> 01:48:53.000
the knowledge he has gained at work?

01:48:53.000 --> 01:48:55.000
Has the knowledge been transformed into skills

01:48:55.000 --> 01:48:57.000
or has it remained?

01:48:57.000 --> 01:48:59.000
We can continue our analogy about football.

01:48:59.000 --> 01:49:01.000
It is very important to know how to play football,

01:49:01.000 --> 01:49:03.000
but never to enter the football field.

01:49:03.000 --> 01:49:05.000
The next level is the assessment

01:49:05.000 --> 01:49:07.000
of the result.

01:49:07.000 --> 01:49:09.000
We are talking about the Kirkpatrick model.

01:49:09.000 --> 01:49:11.000
It is the assessment of the result.

01:49:11.000 --> 01:49:13.000
Does a person achieve

01:49:13.000 --> 01:49:15.000
the result

01:49:15.000 --> 01:49:17.000
for which the training was done?

01:49:17.000 --> 01:49:19.000
Let's see how this model works

01:49:19.000 --> 01:49:21.000
using the example of training.

