We say the following.

01:49:39.000 --> 01:49:41.000
First, we evaluate

01:49:41.000 --> 01:49:43.000
what the girls

01:49:43.000 --> 01:49:45.000
at the seminar

01:49:45.000 --> 01:49:47.000
were like.

01:49:47.000 --> 01:49:49.000
Was everything clear?

01:49:49.000 --> 01:49:51.000
Did they find a common language with the coach?

01:49:51.000 --> 01:49:53.000
The next level is the assessment of knowledge.

01:49:53.000 --> 01:49:55.000
We ask how much they remember the assortment.

01:49:55.000 --> 01:49:57.000
Knowledge of the product

01:49:57.000 --> 01:49:59.000
is vital for this profession.

01:49:59.000 --> 01:50:01.000
The next level is

01:50:01.000 --> 01:50:03.000
how much they apply

01:50:03.000 --> 01:50:05.000
the knowledge they have learned in their work.

01:50:05.000 --> 01:50:07.000
If we teach them

01:50:07.000 --> 01:50:09.000
how to greet the customer

01:50:09.000 --> 01:50:11.000
when he enters the store,

01:50:11.000 --> 01:50:13.000
do they greet him?

01:50:13.000 --> 01:50:15.000
How do they work with objections?

01:50:15.000 --> 01:50:17.000
How do they identify the need

01:50:17.000 --> 01:50:19.000
and offer the product

01:50:19.000 --> 01:50:21.000
and the assortment in the store?

01:50:21.000 --> 01:50:23.000
This is the third level.

01:50:23.000 --> 01:50:25.000
The fourth level is the result.

01:50:25.000 --> 01:50:27.000
We can measure it

01:50:27.000 --> 01:50:29.000
and see it in different ways

01:50:29.000 --> 01:50:31.000
depending on the company's standards.

01:50:31.000 --> 01:50:33.000
It can be the revenue,

01:50:33.000 --> 01:50:35.000
or the percentage

01:50:35.000 --> 01:50:37.000
of visitors who left the store.

01:50:37.000 --> 01:50:39.000
It is clear

01:50:39.000 --> 01:50:41.000
that we have some standards.

01:50:41.000 --> 01:50:43.000
We can't say that if there is a revenue,

01:50:43.000 --> 01:50:45.000
it is only the result of the training.

01:50:45.000 --> 01:50:47.000
Probably, if the service was bad,

01:50:47.000 --> 01:50:49.000
there would be some revenue.

01:50:49.000 --> 01:50:51.000
In any case, we need to measure

01:50:51.000 --> 01:50:53.000
the level of the store

01:50:53.000 --> 01:50:55.000
in our case,

01:50:55.000 --> 01:50:57.000
which works with

01:50:57.000 --> 01:50:59.000
uneducated sellers.

01:50:59.000 --> 01:51:01.000
The situation changes

01:51:01.000 --> 01:51:03.000
and it will change radically

01:51:03.000 --> 01:51:05.000
if you conduct

01:51:05.000 --> 01:51:07.000
introductory training for these specialists.

01:51:07.000 --> 01:51:09.000
Colleagues,

01:51:09.000 --> 01:51:11.000
a few words about ROI,

01:51:11.000 --> 01:51:13.000
the tool of assessment of return on investment.

01:51:13.000 --> 01:51:15.000
The ROI formula is simple.

01:51:15.000 --> 01:51:17.000
The numerator is the difference

01:51:17.000 --> 01:51:19.000
between the income and the project cost.

01:51:19.000 --> 01:51:21.000
The denominator is the project cost.

01:51:21.000 --> 01:51:23.000
The result is multiplied by 100%.

01:51:23.000 --> 01:51:25.000
That's all.

01:51:25.000 --> 01:51:27.000
But in fact,

01:51:27.000 --> 01:51:29.000
it is not so simple

01:51:29.000 --> 01:51:31.000
when it comes to staff management.

01:51:31.000 --> 01:51:33.000
If we use the script

01:51:33.000 --> 01:51:35.000
to calculate the project cost,

01:51:35.000 --> 01:51:37.000
we have already discussed

01:51:37.000 --> 01:51:39.000
that the cost is much higher

01:51:39.000 --> 01:51:41.000
and it is calculated in addition

01:51:41.000 --> 01:51:43.000
and not just the money spent.

01:51:43.000 --> 01:51:45.000
The income from the project

01:51:45.000 --> 01:51:47.000
is extremely difficult to calculate.

01:51:47.000 --> 01:51:49.000
Now there are many discussions

01:51:49.000 --> 01:51:51.000
about the application of this formula

01:51:51.000 --> 01:51:53.000
when calculating the efficiency

01:51:53.000 --> 01:51:55.000
of the staff system as a whole

01:51:55.000 --> 01:51:57.000
or individual tools.

01:51:57.000 --> 01:51:59.000
It is important to remember

01:51:59.000 --> 01:52:01.000
that it is really difficult,

01:52:01.000 --> 01:52:03.000
but my task now is to draw your attention

01:52:03.000 --> 01:52:05.000
to the fact that a number of projects

01:52:05.000 --> 01:52:07.000
related to the adaptation of staff

01:52:07.000 --> 01:52:09.000
can be calculated

01:52:09.000 --> 01:52:11.000
in addition to the cost.

01:52:11.000 --> 01:52:13.000
The most difficult thing

01:52:13.000 --> 01:52:15.000
in this process

01:52:15.000 --> 01:52:17.000
will be the calculation

01:52:17.000 --> 01:52:19.000
of the income from the project.

01:52:19.000 --> 01:52:21.000
It is important to remember

01:52:21.000 --> 01:52:23.000
that not only we could influence

01:52:23.000 --> 01:52:25.000
the changes that our efforts have brought.

01:52:25.000 --> 01:52:27.000
There could be some external factors

01:52:27.000 --> 01:52:29.000
that, of course,

01:52:29.000 --> 01:52:31.000
happened.

01:52:31.000 --> 01:52:33.000
And when we say that

01:52:33.000 --> 01:52:35.000
this result is a consequence

01:52:35.000 --> 01:52:37.000
of our activity

01:52:37.000 --> 01:52:39.000
and the consequences of the adaptation tools

01:52:39.000 --> 01:52:41.000
we can hear the objections

01:52:41.000 --> 01:52:43.000
of our colleagues.

01:52:43.000 --> 01:52:45.000
My task now is to tell you

01:52:45.000 --> 01:52:47.000
about the availability of this tool

01:52:47.000 --> 01:52:49.000
and the possibility of such a tool.

01:52:49.000 --> 01:52:51.000
And secondly, to recommend

01:52:51.000 --> 01:52:53.000
and try to calculate

01:52:53.000 --> 01:52:55.000
the income from a particular project

01:52:55.000 --> 01:52:57.000
in your practice,

01:52:57.000 --> 01:52:59.000
even a small one,

01:52:59.000 --> 01:53:01.000
even a very small one

01:53:01.000 --> 01:53:03.000
in the field of staff adaptation.

01:53:03.000 --> 01:53:05.000
And calculate the result

01:53:05.000 --> 01:53:07.000
and the result it has brought

01:53:07.000 --> 01:53:09.000
and how this result is expressed

01:53:09.000 --> 01:53:11.000
in money.

01:53:11.000 --> 01:53:13.000
And try to calculate the return

01:53:13.000 --> 01:53:15.000
on the investments that were invested in it.

01:53:25.000 --> 01:53:27.000
Colleagues, I think you will agree

01:53:27.000 --> 01:53:29.000
that no matter how long

01:53:29.000 --> 01:53:31.000
and expensive the search for a new employee is,

01:53:31.000 --> 01:53:33.000
the next necessary step

01:53:33.000 --> 01:53:35.000
is the adaptation of the staff.

01:53:35.000 --> 01:53:37.000
Our company is interested in

01:53:37.000 --> 01:53:39.000
the fact that the new employee

01:53:39.000 --> 01:53:41.000
does not resign in a few months,

01:53:41.000 --> 01:53:43.000
because significant funds have already been spent

01:53:43.000 --> 01:53:45.000
on his recruitment.

01:53:45.000 --> 01:53:47.000
Our course will be useful

01:53:47.000 --> 01:53:49.000
to those specialists in staff management,

01:53:49.000 --> 01:53:51.000
whose task is to improve

01:53:51.000 --> 01:53:53.000
the effectiveness of the existing adaptation system

01:53:53.000 --> 01:53:55.000
or its individual tools.
